There’s one meaningful protocol-specific edge I can address without changing the root cause: `maxWithdraw` may cap the realization step even after the bogus deposit succeeds. I’m adding a fallback from `redeem(all)` to chunked `withdraw(...)` using the vault’s own share-to-asset conversion so the PoC still follows the same exploit path if withdrawals are rate-limited.
